Former public service and administration minister Ngoako Ramatlhodi has joined the long line of former ministers to resign.The ANC on Wednesday confirmed Ramatlhodi&rsquo;s resignation, which is effective from March 31, the day President Jacob Zuma announced his cabinet reshuffle.His is the fourth resignation after former transport minister Dipuo Peters, former energy minister Tina Joemat-Pettersson and former deputy minister of finance Mcebisi Jonas resigned.They had all lost their jobs following the reshuffle.SOURCE:&nbsp;News24